          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AREA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The total fission cross sections were",
                "determined from the integrated area under the mass",
                "yield curves.",
                "In order to determine the fractional chain yield for",
                "each nuclide, the cumulative yield for each of their",
                "respective mass chains must be known. For this goal:",
                "  * mass yield curves at 9.3 MeV from Tewes and James",
                " (see REL-REF) normalized to present data at mass",
                " number 83, measured as 83Br;",
                "  * mass yield curve at 11.5 MeV was compiled by",
                "plotting the data for each mass chain given by Tewes",
                "and James (see REL-REF) for 6.3,9.3,13.3, and 17.8 MeV",
                "proton energies and interpolating at 11.3 MeV.",
                " EN-MAX -  Entering energy of beam.",
                " EN-MIN - Emerging energy of beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
