          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AREA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The total fission cross sections were",
                "determined from the integrated area under the mass",
                "yield curves.",
                "In order to determine the fractional chain yield for",
                "each nuclide, the cumulative yield for each of their",
                "respective mass chains must be known. For this goal:",
                "  the mass yield curve for 11.5 MeV deuteron fission",
                "was estimated from the data given by Ramaniah and Wahl",
                " (see REL-REF) for the 9.5 MeV deuteron fission of",
                "252Th. The agreement with these curves was checked by",
                "measuring the cumulative yields of masses 83,",
                "84, 93, 99, 111, 113, 131, and 138.",
                " EN-MAX -  Entering energy of beam.",
                " EN-MIN - Emerging energy of beam."
              ]
            }
